5. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY

The NOESIS DHCF-FNO system, including its:
  - Deterministic Hybrid Control Framework (DHCF) architecture
  - Frozen Neural Operator (FNO) diffusion control methodology
  - CCCS (Cryptographic Control Chain System) subsystem
  - IQS (Integrated Quality Score) v0.9 formula and weighting system
  - 11-stage mastering pipeline design and operator ordering
  - Three-tier LUFS drift contract (PASS / PASS_CF_LIMITED / FAIL)
  - Cryptographic reproducibility system (Snapshot v16+)
  - Genre-aware quality scoring: 33 canonical genres / 144 aliases
  - Stage 8.5 v2 two-pass adaptive pre-limiter algorithm
  - Generation Artifact Guard methodology
  - KAD-integrated quality scoring pipeline
  - Phase-aligned mono bass processing (Theorem C.3)
  - Near-tight FIR crossover design (Theorem C.1)
  - IRC-5 perceptual distortion minimization (Theorem C.2)
  - Chained JSONL tamper-evident audit trail
  - Mastering Merkle Tree (stage-level cryptographic commitment)
  - All mathematical formulas, theorems, and engineering contracts

...are the exclusive intellectual property of Ilia Bolotnikov / AMAImedia.com.

This License does not transfer any ownership, patent rights, or intellectual
property rights to You.


6. GENERATOR AGNOSTICISM

The NOESIS DHCF-FNO framework is designed to be compatible with multiple
AI music generation backends. While the reference implementation uses
ACE-Step v1.5 Turbo as the primary frozen neural operator, the mastering
pipeline, IQS quality scoring, LUFS control, and reproducibility system
are designed to work with any deterministic audio generation backend that
exposes a compatible inference API. This includes, without limitation:
MusicGen, Stable Audio, AudioLDM, Muse, and other audio generation models.
Compatibility with alternative backends does not affect the intellectual
property coverage of this License.


